{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Relevance Scoring and Rerankers for Trustworthy AI & EU AI Act\n",
    "\n",
    "Advanced RAG pipeline for a legal tech company querying:\n",
    "- **Trustworthy AI** podcast transcripts\n",
    "- **EU AI Act** document\n",
    "\n",
    "Pipeline stages:\n",
    "1. Setup & data preparation with metadata\n",
    "2. Embeddings + baseline retrieval (Upstash Vector)\n",
    "3. LLM-based relevance scoring (advanced)\n",
    "4. Cross-Encoder reranker via `sentence-transformers` (advanced, free/local)\n",
    "5. Metadata filtering\n",
    "6. Full RAG pipeline with reranking\n",
    "7. Before/after evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 0: Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%pip install -q openai upstash-vector pypdf requests python-dotenv tiktoken sentence-transformers torch"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Setup & Data Preparation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "from io import BytesIO\n",
    "from typing import List, Dict\n",
    "\n",
    "from openai import OpenAI\n",
    "from upstash_vector import Index\n",
    "from pypdf import PdfReader\n",
    "from sentence_transformers import CrossEncoder\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── API Keys ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "OPENAI_API_KEY = \"YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY\"\n",
    "UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_URL   = \"https://becoming-rodent-13429-eu1-vector.upstash.io\"\n",
    "UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_TOKEN = \"YOUR_UPSTASH_TOKEN"\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "openai_client = OpenAI(api_key=OPENAI_API_KEY)\n",
    "index = Index(url=UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_URL, token=UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_TOKEN)\n",
    "\n",
    "EMBED_MODEL = \"text-embedding-3-small\"  # 1536 dims — matches Upstash index\n",
    "CHAT_MODEL  = \"gpt-4o-mini\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cross-encoder for local reranking (downloads ~70 MB once, then cached)\n",
    "print(\"Loading cross-encoder model...\")\n",
    "cross_encoder = CrossEncoder(\"cross-encoder/ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2\")\n",
    "print(\"✓ All clients initialised\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1a: Load Source Documents\n",
    "\n",
    "Replace the URLs below with the ones your TA provides."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Source URLs (fill in from your TA) ───────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "PODCAST_TRANSCRIPT_URL = \"https://YOUR_TA_PROVIDED_PODCAST_URL\"    # .txt or .pdf\n",
    "EU_AI_ACT_PDF_URL      = \"https://YOUR_TA_PROVIDED_EU_AI_ACT_URL\"  # .pdf\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_pdf_from_url(url: str) -> List[Dict]:\n",
    "    response = requests.get(url, timeout=60)\n",
    "    response.raise_for_status()\n",
    "    reader = PdfReader(BytesIO(response.content))\n",
    "    pages = []\n",
    "    for i, page in enumerate(reader.pages):\n",
    "        text = page.extract_text() or \"\"\n",
    "        if text.strip():\n",
    "            pages.append({\"page\": i + 1, \"text\": text})\n",
    "    return pages\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_text_from_url(url: str) -> str:\n",
    "    response = requests.get(url, timeout=60)\n",
    "    response.raise_for_status()\n",
    "    return response.text\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Loading EU AI Act PDF...\")\n",
    "eu_pages = load_pdf_from_url(EU_AI_ACT_PDF_URL)\n",
    "print(f\"  → {len(eu_pages)} pages loaded\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Loading Podcast Transcript...\")\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    podcast_raw   = load_text_from_url(PODCAST_TRANSCRIPT_URL)\n",
    "    podcast_pages = [{\"page\": 1, \"text\": podcast_raw}]\n",
    "except Exception:\n",
    "    podcast_pages = load_pdf_from_url(PODCAST_TRANSCRIPT_URL)\n",
    "print(f\"  → {len(podcast_pages)} page(s) loaded\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1b: Chunk Documents with Rich Metadata"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def chunk_text(text: str, chunk_size: int = 500, overlap: int = 50) -> List[str]:\n",
    "    words  = text.split()\n",
    "    chunks = []\n",
    "    start  = 0\n",
    "    while start < len(words):\n",
    "        chunks.append(\" \".join(words[start:start + chunk_size]))\n",
    "        start += chunk_size - overlap\n",
    "    return chunks\n",
    "\n",
    "def detect_eu_section(text: str) -> str:\n",
    "    text_upper = text.upper()\n",
    "    for keyword in (\"ARTICLE\", \"CHAPTER\"):\n",
    "        if keyword in text_upper:\n",
    "            idx     = text_upper.find(keyword)\n",
    "            snippet = text[idx:idx + 20].strip()\n",
    "            return snippet.split(\"\\n\")[0]\n",
    "    return \"General\"\n",
    "\n",
    "all_chunks: List[Dict] = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for page_info in eu_pages:\n",
    "    for i, chunk in enumerate(chunk_text(page_info[\"text\"])):\n",
    "        all_chunks.append({\n",
    "            \"text\":        chunk,\n",
    "            \"source\":      \"eu_ai_act\",\n",
    "            \"page\":        page_info[\"page\"],\n",
    "            \"chunk_index\": i,\n",
    "            \"section\":     detect_eu_section(chunk),\n",
    "            \"doc_type\":    \"legal\"\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "for page_info in podcast_pages:\n",
    "    for i, chunk in enumerate(chunk_text(page_info[\"text\"])):\n",
    "        all_chunks.append({\n",
    "            \"text\":        chunk,\n",
    "            \"source\":      \"podcast_transcript\",\n",
    "            \"page\":        page_info[\"page\"],\n",
    "            \"chunk_index\": i,\n",
    "            \"section\":     \"Conversation\",\n",
    "            \"doc_type\":    \"podcast\"\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "eu_count      = sum(1 for c in all_chunks if c[\"source\"] == \"eu_ai_act\")\n",
    "podcast_count = sum(1 for c in all_chunks if c[\"source\"] == \"podcast_transcript\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total chunks : {len(all_chunks)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  EU AI Act  : {eu_count}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Podcast    : {podcast_count}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample metadata:\")\n",
    "print(json.dumps({k: v for k, v in all_chunks[0].items() if k != \"text\"}, indent=2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Generate Embeddings & Store in Upstash Vector"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_embeddings(texts: List[str], batch_size: int = 100) -> List[List[float]]:\n",
    "    all_embeddings = []\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(texts), batch_size):\n",
    "        batch    = texts[i:i + batch_size]\n",
    "        response = openai_client.embeddings.create(model=EMBED_MODEL, input=batch)\n",
    "        all_embeddings.extend([r.embedding for r in response.data])\n",
    "        print(f\"  Embedded {min(i + batch_size, len(texts))}/{len(texts)}\", end=\"\\r\")\n",
    "        time.sleep(0.1)\n",
    "    return all_embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Generating embeddings...\")\n",
    "embeddings = get_embeddings([c[\"text\"] for c in all_chunks])\n",
    "print(f\"\\n✓ {len(embeddings)} embeddings generated (dim={len(embeddings[0])})\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def upsert_to_upstash(chunks: List[Dict], embeddings: List[List[float]], batch_size: int = 100):\n",
    "    vectors = [\n",
    "        (\n",
    "            f\"chunk-{i}\",\n",
    "            emb,\n",
    "            {\n",
    "                \"text\":        chunk[\"text\"][:1000],\n",
    "                \"source\":      chunk[\"source\"],\n",
    "                \"page\":        chunk[\"page\"],\n",
    "                \"chunk_index\": chunk[\"chunk_index\"],\n",
    "                \"section\":     chunk[\"section\"],\n",
    "                \"doc_type\":    chunk[\"doc_type\"]\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        for i, (chunk, emb) in enumerate(zip(chunks, embeddings))\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(vectors), batch_size):\n",
    "        index.upsert(vectors=vectors[i:i + batch_size])\n",
    "        print(f\"  Upserted {min(i + batch_size, len(vectors))}/{len(vectors)}\", end=\"\\r\")\n",
    "        time.sleep(0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Upserting to Upstash Vector...\")\n",
    "upsert_to_upstash(all_chunks, embeddings)\n",
    "print(\"\\n✓ All chunks stored in Upstash Vector\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2a: Baseline Retrieval (no reranking)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def embed_query(query: str) -> List[float]:\n",
    "    return openai_client.embeddings.create(model=EMBED_MODEL, input=[query]).data[0].embedding\n",
    "\n",
    "def baseline_retrieve(query: str, top_k: int = 10, filter_expr: str = None) -> List[Dict]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Pure cosine similarity search — no reranking.\"\"\"\n",
    "    kwargs = {\"vector\": embed_query(query), \"top_k\": top_k, \"include_metadata\": True}\n",
    "    if filter_expr:\n",
    "        kwargs[\"filter\"] = filter_expr\n",
    "    return [\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"id\":       r.id,\n",
    "            \"score\":    r.score,\n",
    "            \"text\":     r.metadata.get(\"text\", \"\"),\n",
    "            \"source\":   r.metadata.get(\"source\", \"\"),\n",
    "            \"section\":  r.metadata.get(\"section\", \"\"),\n",
    "            \"doc_type\": r.metadata.get(\"doc_type\", \"\"),\n",
    "            \"page\":     r.metadata.get(\"page\", \"\"),\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        for r in index.query(**kwargs)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "test_query      = \"What are the requirements for high-risk AI systems?\"\n",
    "baseline_results = baseline_retrieve(test_query, top_k=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Baseline results for: '{test_query}'\\n\")\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(baseline_results, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. [{r['source']}] score={r['score']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   {r['text'][:120]}...\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: LLM-Based Relevance Scoring (Advanced)\n",
    "\n",
    "GPT scores each chunk 0–10 for relevance. The combined score blends vector similarity with the LLM score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RELEVANCE_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a relevance evaluator for a legal AI research system.\n",
    "\n",
    "Query: {query}\n",
    "\n",
    "Chunk:\n",
    "{chunk}\n",
    "\n",
    "Score the relevance of this chunk to the query on a scale of 0 to 10.\n",
    "0 = completely irrelevant, 10 = perfectly answers the query.\n",
    "Respond with ONLY a single integer between 0 and 10. No explanation.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def llm_score_chunk(query: str, chunk_text: str) -> float:\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        resp = openai_client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "            model=CHAT_MODEL,\n",
    "            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": RELEVANCE_PROMPT.format(\n",
    "                query=query, chunk=chunk_text[:800]\n",
    "            )}],\n",
    "            max_tokens=5,\n",
    "            temperature=0\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        return min(max(float(resp.choices[0].message.content.strip()), 0), 10) / 10.0\n",
    "    except Exception:\n",
    "        return 0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "def llm_rerank(query: str, results: List[Dict], alpha: float = 0.5) -> List[Dict]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"combined_score = alpha * vector_score + (1 - alpha) * llm_score\"\"\"\n",
    "    print(f\"LLM scoring {len(results)} chunks...\")\n",
    "    for r in results:\n",
    "        llm_s              = llm_score_chunk(query, r[\"text\"])\n",
    "        r[\"llm_score\"]     = llm_s\n",
    "        r[\"combined_score\"] = alpha * r[\"score\"] + (1 - alpha) * llm_s\n",
    "    return sorted(results, key=lambda x: x[\"combined_score\"], reverse=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_10  = baseline_retrieve(test_query, top_k=10)\n",
    "llm_reranked = llm_rerank(test_query, baseline_10, alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nLLM-reranked results for: '{test_query}'\\n\")\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(llm_reranked[:5], 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. [{r['source']}] vec={r['score']:.3f} | llm={r['llm_score']:.3f} | combined={r['combined_score']:.3f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   {r['text'][:120]}...\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Cross-Encoder Reranker (Advanced — Free & Local)\n",
    "\n",
    "`cross-encoder/ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2` is a dedicated reranker trained on MS MARCO passage ranking.\n",
    "It scores each (query, chunk) pair directly — much more precise than embedding cosine similarity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def cross_encoder_rerank(query: str, results: List[Dict], top_n: int = 5) -> List[Dict]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Rerank using a local cross-encoder model — no API key needed.\"\"\"\n",
    "    pairs  = [[query, r[\"text\"]] for r in results]\n",
    "    scores = cross_encoder.predict(pairs)           # returns numpy array\n",
    "    for r, score in zip(results, scores):\n",
    "        r[\"cross_score\"] = float(score)\n",
    "    reranked = sorted(results, key=lambda x: x[\"cross_score\"], reverse=True)\n",
    "    return reranked[:top_n]\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_10      = baseline_retrieve(test_query, top_k=10)\n",
    "cross_reranked   = cross_encoder_rerank(test_query, baseline_10, top_n=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Cross-encoder reranked results for: '{test_query}'\\n\")\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(cross_reranked, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. [{r['source']}] vec={r['score']:.3f} | cross={r['cross_score']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   {r['text'][:120]}...\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Metadata Filtering\n",
    "\n",
    "Filter retrieval to a specific source (`eu_ai_act` or `podcast_transcript`) using Upstash Vector metadata filters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def retrieve_with_filter(query: str, source_filter: str, top_k: int = 10) -> List[Dict]:\n",
    "    return baseline_retrieve(query, top_k=top_k, filter_expr=f\"source = '{source_filter}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "legal_query   = \"What obligations do providers of high-risk AI systems have?\"\n",
    "podcast_query = \"How do experts discuss AI governance and accountability?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== EU AI Act only ===\")\n",
    "eu_results = retrieve_with_filter(legal_query, \"eu_ai_act\", top_k=5)\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(eu_results, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. [p.{r['page']} | {r['section']}] score={r['score']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   {r['text'][:120]}...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== Podcast only ===\")\n",
    "pod_results = retrieve_with_filter(podcast_query, \"podcast_transcript\", top_k=5)\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(pod_results, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}. [p.{r['page']}] score={r['score']:.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   {r['text'][:120]}...\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6: Complete RAG Pipeline with Reranking\n",
    "\n",
    "The only change from a baseline RAG pipeline is swapping the retrieval step for `cross_encoder_rerank` — a 1-line difference."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RAG_SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a legal AI expert assistant specialising in EU AI regulation and AI ethics.\n",
    "Answer questions using ONLY the provided context chunks.\n",
    "If the context doesn't contain enough information, say so.\n",
    "Cite your sources by mentioning the document name and section.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def rag_answer(query: str, context_chunks: List[Dict]) -> str:\n",
    "    context = \"\\n\\n---\\n\\n\".join([\n",
    "        f\"[Source: {c['source']} | Page {c['page']} | {c['section']}]\\n{c['text']}\"\n",
    "        for c in context_chunks\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    resp = openai_client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=CHAT_MODEL,\n",
    "        messages=[\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": RAG_SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{context}\\n\\nQuestion: {query}\"}\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        temperature=0.2\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return resp.choices[0].message.content\n",
    "\n",
    "def full_rag_pipeline(\n",
    "    query: str,\n",
    "    source_filter: str = None,\n",
    "    use_cross_encoder: bool = True,\n",
    "    use_llm_scoring:   bool = False,\n",
    "    top_k_retrieve:    int  = 10,\n",
    "    top_n_rerank:      int  = 5\n",
    ") -> Dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"End-to-end RAG: retrieve → (filter) → rerank → generate.\"\"\"\n",
    "    results = (\n",
    "        retrieve_with_filter(query, source_filter, top_k=top_k_retrieve)\n",
    "        if source_filter\n",
    "        else baseline_retrieve(query, top_k=top_k_retrieve)\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    if use_cross_encoder:\n",
    "        reranked = cross_encoder_rerank(query, results, top_n=top_n_rerank)  # ← the 1-line swap\n",
    "    elif use_llm_scoring:\n",
    "        reranked = llm_rerank(query, results)[:top_n_rerank]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        reranked = results[:top_n_rerank]\n",
    "\n",
    "    answer = rag_answer(query, reranked)\n",
    "    return {\"query\": query, \"answer\": answer, \"chunks_used\": reranked}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Demo\n",
    "demo_query = \"What are the key obligations for providers of high-risk AI systems under the EU AI Act?\"\n",
    "result     = full_rag_pipeline(demo_query, source_filter=\"eu_ai_act\", use_cross_encoder=True)\n",
    "print(f\"Q: {result['query']}\\n\")\n",
    "print(f\"A: {result['answer']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7: Evaluate Performance — Before vs After Reranking\n",
    "\n",
    "Three pipelines compared across 5 queries:\n",
    "- **Baseline** — pure vector similarity\n",
    "- **LLM Scored** — GPT relevance scoring\n",
    "- **Cross-Encoder** — local reranker (ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2)\n",
    "\n",
    "Manually rate each answer 1–5 after reviewing the outputs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "TEST_QUERIES = [\n",
    "    {\"query\": \"What are the requirements for high-risk AI systems under the EU AI Act?\",  \"filter\": \"eu_ai_act\"},\n",
    "    {\"query\": \"How should AI systems handle human oversight?\",                             \"filter\": None},\n",
    "    {\"query\": \"What does the EU AI Act say about transparency obligations?\",               \"filter\": \"eu_ai_act\"},\n",
    "    {\"query\": \"How do podcast guests discuss AI bias and fairness?\",                       \"filter\": \"podcast_transcript\"},\n",
    "    {\"query\": \"What penalties exist for non-compliance with the EU AI Act?\",               \"filter\": \"eu_ai_act\"},\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "evaluation_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for item in TEST_QUERIES:\n",
    "    q, f = item[\"query\"], item[\"filter\"]\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*70}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Query : {q}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Filter: {f or 'none (all sources)'}\")\n",
    "    print('='*70)\n",
    "\n",
    "    pool         = retrieve_with_filter(q, f, 10) if f else baseline_retrieve(q, 10)\n",
    "    chunks_base  = pool[:5]\n",
    "    chunks_cross = cross_encoder_rerank(q, pool[:], top_n=5)   # fresh copy\n",
    "    chunks_llm   = llm_rerank(q, [dict(r) for r in pool])[:5]  # fresh copy\n",
    "\n",
    "    ans_base  = rag_answer(q, chunks_base)\n",
    "    ans_cross = rag_answer(q, chunks_cross)\n",
